description:
job responsibilities
• develop real time 3d renderer on multiple platforms including pc, console and mobile.
• develop 3d rendering features such as pbr, volumetric rendering, global illumination, reflection, skin&hair rendering, post-process effects.
• develop and customize offline render and tools such as ue light mass.

job requirements
• minimum 2 years developing experience on video game, cg, animation, movies;
• strong foundation in mathematics, such as calculus, linear algebra, geometry, numerical method;
• strong foundation in 3d graphics, such as curves & surface, color space?brdf?light transport etc;
• strong foundation in programming, expert on c/c++, shading languages(osl/hlsl/glsl/cg);
• good knowledge of graphics api(directx/opengl(es)/metal/vulkan);
• good knowledge of gpgpu(opencl/cuda), experience on parallel programming;
• good communication skills that support an open and enthusiastic working environment.

job responsibilities

· facilitating deal origination and execution including sourcing, valuation, and negotiation of investment projects across major european countries;
· presenting investment opportunities to leadership teams, identify and discuss key drivers of value, and conduct necessary research to verify hypotheses;
· conducting research into potential new areas of investment, and formulating new strategies for investment areas, including market sizing, surveys, interviews, and extensive data analysis;
· partner with deal teams, leaders and business groups to formulate investment strategies and post-deal management strategies; including working with cross functional teams to manage deal processes, finance monitoring, business analysis, business cooperation, valuation adjustments, supporting board meetings, and handling related documentation;
· maintain a strong network of quality relationship across wide ecosystem of founders, investors, colleagues and other stakeholders；
· comfortable handling a large volume of work, with a positive attitude, in a matrixed organization.

job requirements

· high level of integrity, curiosity, dedication and motivation;
· bachelor/master’s degree;
· over 3 years working experience in private equity, venture capital, hedge fund, banking (ibd, m&a, corporate finance), other buy side investing organizations, or in a corporate development role at strategic investor;
· familiarity with consumer internet, digital content, gaming, fintech, enterprise software, health care, and/or other vertical investment areas;
. strong interest, passion and business sense for internet, investment and tencent;
· hard working, down-to-earth, mature and team-oriented;
· strong analytical, communication and negotiation skills；
· financial modeling skills

